Author: db71
Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: Unfortunately this withdraw issue is a Cryptopia error and they put the wallet in maintenance. That's why both deposit as withdraw are now not possible. If you sent CORIONS before the maintenance, then your coins are stuck and Cryptopia must come with a solution. If you sent CORIONS to Cryptopia while the wallet was already in maintenance, then your coins are at Cryptopia, but not in your balance yet.  The CORION foundation has no influence but trying to contact Cryptopia, but for the rest it's Cryptopia who must act. I got a reply on my support ticket:  My question:  Quote Hi there, I did withdraw over 282 CORIONS and send them to my CORION wallet, but the coins never arrived. At gastracker.io (http://gastracker.io/tx/0xd753fd972872b181ab70db29bb6a5aade8e091e0f61c2d14ce5dcc31819cca50) I see Failed for the transaction, but where are my coin now? The transaction details: #   Currency   Amount   Fee   Status TransactionId   Address   Timestamp 910225   COR   282.93201850   0.01000000   Complete   0xd753fd972872b181ab70db29bb6a5aade8e091e0f61c2d14ce5dcc31819cca50   0xa170c84f74dac6b05888ffc0f3a5b181e53226bd   5/10/2017 6:26:00 PM The CORION address is double-double checked. Regards  Cryptopia reply:  Quote Hi db71,  Thanks for contacting Cryptopia.  Thanks for letting us know about this, I've escalated this to our admins and they'll look into it the first chance they get. I'd like to ask for your continued patience as we work towards getting to this one - we're really busy at the moment!  I'll leave this ticket open and we'll get back to you once we know more. Thanks once again for your patience!  Kind regards,   Cryptopia Support  A few days after the reply they set the wallet in maintenance with this message:  Quote Investigating withdraw issues.

Author: Mesterlovesz1974
Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: Hello CORION Community! As we promised, we are starting to enable the functions of the CORION Platform! From now on you can transfer your Corion coins to any wallet. If anyone want to sell or buy CORION, then simply post your buy or sell order here or at any forum group! If anyone want to create a new wallet you can do it now.  Here is the full ist of the features we enabled now:   - CORION transaction is available from the Wallet  - Signup is available (Twitter bounty winners can register from now)  - QR scan and upload available  - GasStation for purchase of 0,2 ETC as GAS for CORION  - Generate new COR/ETC address  - Import existing COR/ETC address  - Backup address  - Delete address (watch out with this one, make backup first)  The next function will be the provider. It will happen next week.

Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: As far I understand the supply of coins increase when the demand rise. But what when the demand decline?  Would the coins be burned then?  Because otherwise the price stability works only upwards So in what way the price is protected downwards?

Author: Mesterlovesz1974
Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: Yes, the answer is there in the White Paper. The automated stabilization process is releasing new coins when there is demand for the coin and will stop the coin release when there is a surplus on the coin. And every time when a transaction occur, 80% of the transaction fees are burning, never coming back to the system.

Author: Mesterlovesz1974
Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: Anyone who has been following the cryptocurrency market should already be aware of the recent malicious attacks against popular wallets – several of which were successful, and resulted in drastic losses to their users.    At CORION, we understand the seriousness of these threats, and decided to invite several highly-trusted security experts to review the CORION system. We wanted to make sure our code is not only bullet-proof, but also hacker-proof.  The surprising result? We have located a vulnerability unknown so far which creates a backdoor to the affected wallets, allowing hackers to circumvent the security of these systems, and gain access.    What is even more shocking is that one doesn't even need to be a hacker to exploit this vulnerability, and gain access to your wallet.  Turns out, due to the lack of industry standards for the creation and set-up of a fortified wallet, most are not nearly as secure as they claim to be. Our investigation suggests that this newly-exposed security hazard actually affects the majority of wallets currently available to users.  http://blog.corion.io/media/corion-ico-announcement/

Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: We have a capable team who created the webpage. We had some point of view we would like to implement on it.  There is no peg behind Corion. It is an automated process which keeps the price stable. Also of course at the begining while our community is relatively small there can be some whale movements, up or down, so the Foundation may have to intervene. But as our community grows, there will be more and more coins every day, so whales can not shake the price. Or if they try, the automated process will be enough to handle that.  Tether and Nubits do not have these 3 layers we implemented in, so when there was a problem they had to use their reserves to keep up and yes, reserves can be drained easily. If you have only that then your system is created for doom.

Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: The Reasons why Corion Token/Coins will be one of the Most Popular Cryptocurrency in the world for many years to come...  (1) Corion Tokens/Coins is hosted on the Ethereum Classic Blockchain. One of the very first Cryptocurrency on it.  (2) ICO BONUSES  (3) Corion Platform Smart Contract Base, Built-in Decentralised P2P exchange provides a SAFE, FAST, and SECURE entry point. Can't be HACKED like DAO.  (4) Corion don't Fluctuate like other Smart Contract CryptoTokens or CryptoCurrencies Thus, It value is maintained E.g. each Corion coin value $1 today will maintain  $1 in 2018 ..so on This will help Market Traders, Ecommerce Merchants maintain value for their capital accepting Corions as means of payment. YOU MAY ASK THEN HOW I CAN MAKE PROFIT ON CORION?  (5) CORION ACTIVITIES REWARD DAILY COIN EMISSION.. They are 2 Service Provider on the Corion Platform .. PUBLIC SERVICE PROVIDER PRIVATE PUBLIC PROVIDER  The Amount of Wallet Connected to a Public Service Provider is UNLIMITED for the daily coin emission  While  The Amount of Wallet Connected to a Private Service Provider is just 250 for the daily coin emission  The Public Service Provider will require a purchase of 3,000corions ($3,000) to be ACTIVE  The Private Service Provider will require a purchase of 8,000corions ($8,000) to be ACTIVE  All Corion Wallets are either CONNECTED to A PUBLIC SERVICE PROVIDER  or A PRIVATE SERVICE PROVIDER for 0-2.5% daily coin emission reward..  The Public Service Provider sets his daily coin emission reward from 30% minimum and 70% maximum. While The Private Service Provider sets his daily coin emission reward to 0% minimum or 100% Maximum.  The daily coin emission reward can be aquired daily to each corion wallet holder base on the numbers of Corion coins in their wallet and already set daily emission reward of the Service Provider their are connected to ..  E.g...  A PUBLIC SERVICE PROVIDER who has set his emission reward to 50%-50% (50% for him, 50% for his connected wallet holders) is connected to 200 Corion Wallet Account Holders with each of them having 500corion coins each .. The Emission Reward for the day is 2.5%  Both Provider and Wallet Holder will get 6.25corions ($6.25) each .. Meaning the Wallet holder will have 500 + 6.25 =506.25corions ($506.25). The next day emission reward will base on 506.25corions  The PROVIDER gets 6.25corions ($6.25) each on each of the 200 Corion Wallet Connected to his Network as coin emission reward for the day. 6.25 X 200 = 1,250corions ($1,250) to be added to his own account for that trading day alone  By Assumption: 1,250 X 30days = 37,500corions ($37,500)monthly This could be more base on Power of Compounding and also as his Network grows from 200 connected wallet to more..

Author: Mesterlovesz1974
Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: Hmmm. This is not a charity. We are not giving away free money.  Service providers are businessmen who already have or would like to start a business and have enough money to do so. If you have your own business already then you can extend your business to the crypto world, where you can find more customers and/or a funding source for your business.  If you are starting your own business then you can have this second layer where you can find funding for the start of your business or extra source of money.  So how you can find your users, customers?  In an indirect way, you just put your business on our platform (by reserving 3000 or 8000 Corions, which is redeemable after you stop being a service provider). It means you will be in our Marketplace and if users find your business offer and/or giveback percentage attractive then they will connect to you.  I a direct way, you can promote your own business among your regular customers, maybe offer discount if they pay with Corion, or just ask them to support you. Or you can come up with some alternative, like you start a contest, if the monthly income from Corion will be higher than (that number) then you will give 20% discount for all Corion buyers.

Title: [ANN][COR]CORION Platform Gateway to the Crypto World! ICO, Bounty Campaign
Body: Slack invite link is ready now, use it from the first page!  The Buying Process:  The ‘BUYING PROCESS’ Go to https://corion.io/buy   and follow the ‘buying process’  There are 3 steps:  Decide on the amount of CORIONs you want to buy and also the currency you want to use to pay  (BTC, ETH, ETC).  If you find the numbers correct, click on NEXT to go on.  On he top side of this page you will find the Public address where you have to send the currency you will use to pay. At the bottom of the page you can set the CORION (ETC) public address. As default  we will generate your CORION (ETC) public address and display the corresponding vital information like private key, brainwallet and backup file.  If you want to use your existing ETC address, choose “I have an ETC address” opction and write it in the field that pops up below. IMPORTANT ! we do not save and store private keys, that is why save all the data that appear under ‘Private Details’  for yourself.  When you have set all the values as you wanted, click on NEXT to continue on page 3.   3.   On this page you can register your  CORION Wallet account . It is important to do so because this will ensure you the  access to all the features of the platform.  After you registered, and 3-6 hours passed, check your balance at www.corion.io/wallet
